Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Motion to Unseal Search Warrant Affidavit, filed.

Defendant Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez appeared by video.  Attorney Mindy M. Nolan in court for Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez.  Prosecuting attorney Jon R Josephsen Jr. for Patrick Franken in court for the State of Wisconsin. 

Spanish Interpreter sworn:  Natalia Fajardo, appearing by video.

Case in Court for Scheduling conference.  Defense awaiting unsealing of warrant to discuss possible motions with the Defendant. Court advised there are no pending requests for substitution. Court finds good cause to adjourn this matter for further scheduling conference.  Defendant advised to appear in person for next hearing.  Spanish interpreter requested. Case adjourned to Br. 9. Scheduling conference scheduled for December 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez in court.  Attorney Mindy M. Nolan in court for Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez.  Attorney Owen Piotrowski for Patrick T. Franken in court for State of Wisconsin. Defense waives Spanish interpreter. Case in court for scheduling conference. Court finds that substitution not granted due to co-defendant cases. Case sent back to Br. 9 Case adjourned in Branch 9.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and filed:  Original Transcript of Proceedings commencing 8/19/2022  (13 pages) and Certification of Filing Transcript.

Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Van Grunsven.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Hanrahan, Br. 04.
Sworn as Spanish interpreters: Natalie Fajardo and Reme Rashi

Defendant Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez in court in person.  Attorney Mindy M. Nolan in court in person for Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Officer N. Grap. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 04.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant's Request for Substitution of Judge, filed.

Defendant previously posted $7,500 cash bail. Court orders cash bail returned to the remitter. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Imeida J Lopez-Bojorquez in court with attorney Mindy M. Nolan.  Thomas L. Potter, along with student intern Joshua Kather under the student practice rule, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sworn as interpreter: Orlando Penate
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Van Grunsven, Branch 09.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  
Defense motions to dismiss. Arguements heard.
Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings. Court DENIES Defense's motion.
Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
